\nI'm looking at the current factory setup, which uses sslConnection.getDecryptedEndPoint, but it’s not opening. Maybe upgrading to a safer direct ByteArrayEndPoint is a good idea? But that's not compatible with JDK9. I think adding a validation test for ALPNClientConnectionFactory could work since it will be public from the existing dependency. The source \\\"jetty-alpn-java-client\\\" only has one direct class that’s already covered in functional code. It seems like it’s a potential new feature that could be untested. I need to focus on editing and adding that test and helper.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nlNOtGN3EiRTSLldopjUMdyM|fc_03f3ae52c9c63f9f016a01f9b7593481a18b52a867c2b7f8c2", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-alpn-java-client/11.0.24/src/test/java/org_eclipse_jetty/jetty_alpn_java_client/Jetty_alpn_java_clientTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void clientConnectionFactoryRejectsSslEnginesThatNoLoadedProcessorAppliesTo() {\n        ALPNClientConnectionFactory factory = new ALPNClientConnectionFactory(\n                DIRECT_EXECUTOR,\n                new TestClientConnectionFactory(),\n                PROTOCOLS);\n        Map<String, Object> context = new HashMap<>();\n        TestSslEngine sslEngine = new TestSslEngine(null);\n        context.put(SslClientConnectionFactory.SSL_ENGINE_CONTEXT_KEY, sslEngine);\n\n        assertThatExceptionOfType(IllegalStateException.class)\n                .isThrownBy(() -> factory.newConnection(new ByteArrayEndPoint(), context))\n                .withMessage(\"No ALPNProcessor for \" + sslEngine);\n    }\n\n    private static ALPNTestContext newALPNTestContext(TestSslEngine sslEngine) {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void clientConnectionFactoryRejectsSslEnginesThatNoLoadedProcessorAppliesTo() {\n        ALPNClientConnectionFactory factory = new ALPNClientConnectionFactory(\n                DIRECT_EXECUTOR,\n                new TestClientConnectionFactory(),\n                PROTOCOLS);\n        Map<String, Object> context = new HashMap<>();\n        TestSslEngine sslEngine = new TestSslEngine(null);\n        context.put(SslClientConnectionFactory.SSL_ENGINE_CONTEXT_KEY, sslEngine);\n\n        assertThatExceptionOfType(IllegalStateException.class)\n                .isThrownBy(() -> factory.newConnection(new ByteArrayEndPoint(), context))\n                .withMessage(\"No ALPNProcessor for \" + sslEngine);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void selectedProtocolUpgradesEndPointToNegotiatedClientConnection() throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayEndPoint endPoint = new ByteArrayEndPoint();\n        SSLEngine sslEngine = newClientEngine();\n        Map<String, Object> context = new HashMap<>();\n        CapturingClientConnectionFactory connectionFactory = new CapturingClientConnectionFactory();\n        ALPNClientConnection alpnConnection = new ALPNClientConnection(\n                endPoint,\n                DIRECT_EXECUTOR,\n                connectionFactory,\n                sslEngine,\n                context,\n                PROTOCOLS);\n        endPoint.setConnection(alpnConnection);\n\n        alpnConnection.selected(\"h2\");\n        alpnConnection.onOpen();\n\n        assertThat(alpnConnection.getProtocol()).isEqualTo(\"h2\");\n        assertThat(connectionFactory.endPoints).containsExactly(endPoint);\n        assertThat(connectionFactory.contexts).containsExactly(context);\n        assertThat(endPoint.getConnection()).isInstanceOf(RecordingConnection.class);\n        endPoint.close();\n    }\n\n    private static ALPNTestContext newALPNTestContext(TestSslEngine sslEngine) {\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class TestClientConnectionFactory implements ClientConnectionFactory {\n        @Override\n        public Connection newConnection(EndPoint endPoint, Map<String, Object> context) {\n            return new RecordingConnection(endPoint);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingConnection extends AbstractConnection {\n", "newText": "    private static final class TestClientConnectionFactory implements ClientConnectionFactory {\n        @Override\n        public Connection newConnection(EndPoint endPoint, Map<String, Object> context) {\n            return new RecordingConnection(endPoint);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class CapturingClientConnectionFactory implements ClientConnectionFactory {\n        private final List<EndPoint> endPoints = new ArrayList<>();\n        private final List<Map<String, Object>> contexts = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        @Override\n        public Connection newConnection(EndPoint endPoint, Map<String, Object> context) {\n            endPoints.add(endPoint);\n            contexts.add(context);\n            return new RecordingConnection(endPoint);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingConnection extends AbstractConnection {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 905, "output": 1887, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32488, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778514341338, "responseId": "resp_03f3ae52c9c63f9f016a01f9a6173081a19030ffe90ea904ab"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_nlNOtGN3EiRTSLldopjUMdyM|fc_03f3ae52c9c63f9f016a01f9b7593481a18b52a867c2b7f8c2", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-alpn-java-client/11.0.24/src/test/java/org_eclipse_jetty/jetty_alpn_java_client/Jetty_alpn_java_clientTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n 135                 .isThrownBy(() -> factory.newConnection(new ByteArrayEndPoint(), context))\n 136                 .withMessage(\"No ALPNProcessor for \" + sslEngine);\n 137     }\n 138 \n+139     @Test\n+140     void selectedProtocolUpgradesEndPointToNegotiatedClientConnection()